    </extensions>
  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="37.14722" lon="-91.44972">
    <name>ALLEY SPRING</name>
    <desc>Overview The rolling, forested landscape around Alley Spring is where two of America&apos;s most beautiful spring-fed rivers combine to make up the Ozark National Scenic Riverways. As the first national park area to protect a wild river system, visitors are able to enjoy various water activities as well as hiking, horseback riding and wildlife viewing. Recreation Canoeing, tubing, swimming and fishing are popular activities on the vast waterways in the region, with over 130 miles (209 km) of water tr...</desc>
