    <desc>The Big Piney Ranger District hosts a wide variety of cultural and natural history, recreational opportunities, timber, range, mineral reserves, and wildlife. It contains 449,000 acres of snow-capped mountain peaks, lush vegetation and clear mountain lakes and streams. The district maintains 300 miles of system trails, 25 permitted summer and fall outfitters, 11 summer homes and one developed campground. 10418 South US Highway 189 P.O. Box 218 Big Piney, WY 83113 307-276-5800 Fax 307-276-5203 Of...</desc>
