    <name>Brush Creek/Hayden Ranger District</name>
    <desc>The Brush Creek/Hayden Ranger District office outside Saratoga, Wyoming oversees the Sierra Madre Range and west side of the Snowy Range. Maps, passes and Forest product permits are available for purchase at the office. The Brush Creek Visitor Center is 20 miles southeast of Saratoga on Highway 130 and is open from Memorial Day through Labor Day annually. Select Sierra Madre or Snowy Range under &apos;Areas &amp; Activities&apos; in the right-hand sidebar to find recreation sites on the Brush Creek/Hayden Ran...</desc>
