    <desc>Recommended Users: Hikers. Singletrack trail. 0.3 miles in length. Difficulty: Easy. This short section of trail was once a section of the historic water canal. The tunnels connecting the Canal Trail around the drainage are now too dangerous for use (hence the trail re-route dropping down to the river and back up the other side of the drainage). At the end of the China Town Flume trail, are the remains of the flume that carried the water across the drainage. DO NOT continue past the chainlink fe...</desc>
