    <desc>The Conasauga Ranger District covers the western third of the Chattahoochee National Forest. A diverse set of landscapes make up the Conasauga district, from the ridges and valleys west of Interstate 75 to the Cohutta Mountains northeast of Chatsworh, GA. As you&apos;ll find in the links below, this part of the forest offers some of the best scenery and outdoor recreational activities in north Georgia.</desc>
