    <desc>A popular semi-primitive campground adjacent to the Cranberry River and the &quot;lower-gate&quot; entrance to the Cranberry Backcountry. This campground receives very high use during trout stocking from the beginning of spring through the end of June and again in the fall from September through October. During these high use times there are usually more campers waiting than there are sites available. During high use, the centrally located Bishop Knob Campground can usually accommodate campers when no sit...</desc>
