    <name>Ely Ranger District Office</name>
    <desc>The Ely Ranger District makes up approximately 1.1 million acres of the Humboldt-Toiyabe National Forest and extends over three Nevada counties: Nye, White Pine and Lincoln. Ely, Nevada, located in the heart of the District, is the nearest town and houses the District office. The District lies approximately 240 miles north of Las Vegas, Nevada, via I-15, State Highways 93, 318 and 6; and 190 miles south of Elko, Nevada, via I-80 and State Highway 93. If you have questions for comments please con...</desc>
