    <desc>Overview Hackberry Pavilion is an excellent place for visitors to spend the day at Lavon Lake, enjoying the beach, picnicking and boating. Recreation Lavon Lake&apos;s most common fish include the largemouth bass, white bass, blue catfish and crappie. Horseback riding and hiking is sublime on the nearby Trinity Trail. Facilities The picnic pavilion holds a whopping 500 guests and the sandy swimming beach is a big hit during warm months. Natural Features The pavilion is located in Avalon Park, on the ...</desc>
