    <name>Moccasin Mountain Dinosaur Tracksite</name>
    <desc>The Moccasin Mountain Dinosaur Tracksite is one of Utah’s most significant fossil track localities located on BLM-managed lands near Kanab. Visitors can explore the track-bearing surfaces on foot and learn from interpretive panels that explain the geology, paleontology, and importance of protecting these fragile resources. The site’s remote setting provides expansive views of Navajo Sandstone and surrounding high-desert terrain. The site preserves hundreds of fossilized dinosaur and other verteb...</desc>
