    <desc>Follow State Route 20 east and view one of the largest populations of bald eagles in the United States along the Skagit River. Five native salmon species and sea-going trout attract the eagles to the Skagit River. State Route 20 eventually travels into the heart of the neighboring North Cascades National Park. Explore the Skagit Wild and Scenic River System Segments of the Skagit, Sauk, Suiattle and Cascade Rivers make up the federally designated Skagit Wild &amp; Scenic River System. Launch your bo...</desc>
