  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="44.500575" lon="-120.3871861">
    <name>OCHOCO DIVIDE GROUP SITE</name>
    <desc>Overview The Ochoco Divide Group Site is a convenient place to camp while traveling across scenic State Highway 26 by bicycle or car. Resting at the top of the Ochoco Divide at an elevation of 4,700 ft., the group site is set on a hill away from the road as an extension of the general campground. Summertime in the Ochoco National Forest brings pleasant temperatures; the campground is closed during winter. Recreation The group site of the Ochoco Divide Campground is mainly used by touring cyclist...</desc>
