  <wpt lat="40.742166" lon="-109.623593">
    <name>Oaks Park Campground</name>
    <desc>There are 11 campsites on the south shore of large and lovely Oaks Park Reservoir. There is a pump handle well on the west shore of the reservoir. Trails lead north from the lake, and the area is open to OHV use. A trail leads south from the campground to the Big Brush Creek Cave. If you are interested in caving, please contact the Forest Service.</desc>
