    <name>PANGUITCH LAKE</name>
    <desc>Overview Panguitch Lake Campground is located 14 miles southwest of Panguitch, Utah. Some of the state&apos;s largest rainbow trout are fished from the lake each year, and aptly so; &quot;Panguitch&quot; comes from the Paiute word meaning &quot;big fish.&quot; Visitors also enjoy canoeing and exploring the Panguitch Lake OHV Trail System. Recreation Panguitch Lake offers great fishing for rainbow, brook, cutthroat and brown trout. Canoeing and kyacking are a popular activity. Two public boat ramps are located on the lak...</desc>
