    <desc>Priest Lake was originally called Roothaan Lake by Father Desmet in 1846 in honor of his Jesuit Superior in Rome. One of the prominent peaks in the Selkirk Range still bears the name Roothaan. In 1865, Captain John Mullan designated this same lake as Kaniksu Lake on one of his maps. It is believed that &quot;Kaniksu&quot; was the Indian name of Black Robe, although this has never been authenticated. The name was gradually changed in the early 1900&apos;s from Kaniksu Lake to its present name of Priest Lake, wh...</desc>
