    <name>RAY BEHRENS</name>
    <desc>Overview Ray Behrens is a scenic campground and recreation area, conveniently located on the southeastern shores of Mark Twain Lake. Here, visitors can enjoy the perks of the campground, go boating on the lake or explore the area&apos;s historic attractions. Twain, the legendary author, was born in a village beside the lake and grew up in a town about 20 miles down the road. Recreation Mark Twain Lake provides countless opportunities for outdoor recreation – boating, swimming, fishing, picnicking, ca...</desc>
