    <desc>Stocked annually with trout, Smith Reservoir makes a good fishing spot. Boats can be launched from a site near the dam (a 10 mile per hour speed limit for boats is enforced). Lakes End Campground is the one campground located on the reservoir and is accessible only by boat. Beautiful Sahalie and Koosah Falls are nearby on the McKenzie River National Recreation Trail . The reservoir when full, spans 170 acres. In late summer, early fall through mid-March, the water levels on Smith Reservoir are f...</desc>
