    <name>South Platte River Corridor</name>
    <desc>The South Platte River Corridor near Deckers, CO has been a popular fishing location for decades. In the 1890&apos;s, Stephen Decker built a general store and later a saloon in this area. The South Platte Hotel, located at the confluence of the North Fork of the South Platte, was a popular resort in the early 1900&apos;s and was accessible only by train. The confluence provides access for fishing, kayaking, and trail use . The South Platte River is part of a 1.6 million-acre watershed that reaches from th...</desc>
