  <wpt lat="40.042055" lon="-122.980957">
    <name>Yolla Bolly-Middle Eel Wilderness</name>
    <desc>In the Wintun Indian language, &quot;Yo-la&quot; means &quot;snow covered&quot;, and &quot;Bo-li&quot; means &quot;high peak.&quot; The second part of this Wilderness&apos; name refers to the headwaters of the Middle Fork Eel River, which originates in this remote and rugged land. This area was first protected in 1931 when it was classified as a primitive area. Further protection was given when this area became part of the National Wilderness Preservation System, created by the passage of the Wilderness Act of 1964. The Wilderness Act of 1...</desc>
    <type>Camping</type>
    <sym>Campground</sym>
